20car%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFranzone%20committed%20his%20crime%20by%20exploiting%20the%20networks%20and%20connections%20in%20the%20NASCAR%20community%2C%26quot%3B%20from%20coast%20to%20coast%20and%20in%20England%2C%20prosecutors%20wrote%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20say%20Franzone's%20victims%20include%20racing%20legend%20and%201995%20NASCAR%20truck%20series%20champion%20Mike%20%26quot%3BThe%20Gunslinger%26quot%3B%20Skinner.%20And%20they%20say%20Franzone%20used%20the%20fund%20to%20finance%20a%20flashy%2C%20high-octane%20racing%20lifestyle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20Franzone%20illegally%20spent%20%24565%2C000%20in%20fund%20assets%20to%20purchase%20an%20airplane%20hangar%20just%20outside%20Daytona%20Beach%2C%20prosecutors%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hangar%20housed%20Franzone's%20prized%20vintage%20race%20car%20collection%2C%20including%20Skinner's%20series-winning%20Chevy%20truck%20and%20the%20Ford%20Galaxie%20that%20Fred%20%26quot%3BGolden%20Boy%26quot%3B%20Lorenzen%20drove%20to%20victory%20in%20the%201965%20Daytona%20500%2C%20according%20to%20a%202016%20profile%20in%20the%20Wall%20Street%20Journal.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20the%20coolest%20sound%20I'd%20ever%20heard%2C%26quot%3B%20Franzone%20told%20the%20Journal%2C%20describing%20being%20in%20his%2020s%20and%20hearing%20the%20engine%20roar%20of%20%26quot%3Ban%20old%201960s%20big%20block%20stock%20car%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20say%20the%20hangar%20was%20also%20home%20to%20Franzone's%20racing%20team%2C%20ATF%20%26amp%3B%20Gunslinger.%20Skinner%20was%20a%20celebrity%20driver%20for%20the%20team.%20So%20was%20five-time%20pro-wrestling%20world%20champion%20Bill%20Goldberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EATF%20%26amp%3B%20Gunslinger%20proved%20a%20success%2C%20winning%20races%20in%20the%20US%20and%20UK.%20In%202017%2C%20Hard%20Rock%20International%2C%20the%20global%20caf%C3%A9%20and%20hotel%20chain%2C%20signed%20on%20as%20a%20sponsor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20in%202019%2C%20investors%20became%20jittery%2C%20questioning%20Franzone's%20alleged%20lies%20about%20his%20fund's%20liquidity%20and%20performance%2C%20and%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20words%20of%20prosecutors%20%E2%80%94%20his%20%26quot%3Bhouse%20of%20cards%26quot%3B%20collapsed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225ba2aef4-d774-4903-8e79-e892d7047a30%5C%22%3EFrom%20stock%20cars%20to%20stock%20fraud%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20a%20criminal%20defendant%20%E2%80%94%20who%20used%20the%20New%20York%20City%20subway%20to%20travel%20to%20his%20most%20recent%20court%20date%20%E2%80%94%20Franzone%20has%20fought%2C%20without%20luck%2C%20to%20keep%20any%20reference%20to%20NASCAR%20and%20race%20cars%20out%20of%20his%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Franzone's%20last%20day%20in%20court%2C%20on%20April%207%2C%20defense%20attorney%20Joseph%20R.%20Corozzo%20argued%20that%20references%20to%20his%20client's%20spending%20on%20his%20racing%20hobby%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bunduly%20prejudicial.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20be%20like%20telling%20jurors%2C%20%26quot%3BHis%20spending%20is%20on%20race%20cars%2C%20so%20you%20should%20be%20offended%2C%26quot%3B%20Corozzo%20argued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20ruling%20Thursday%2C%20US%20District%20Judge%20Vernon%20Broderick%20disagreed.%20The%20judge%20wrote%20that%20evidence%20of%20Franzone's%20spending%20and%20lifestyle%20%26quot%3Bis%20probative%20of%20his%20motive%20to%20commit%20the%20fraud%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20therefore%20fair%20game%20for%20jurors%20to%20hear%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d0e0a5ba-c208-46b9-b8d4-3dfad0f22919%5C%22%3EA%20%26quot%3Bromantic%20partner%26quot%3B%20and%20luxury%20vehicles%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFranzone%20was%20so%20obsessed%20with%20maintaining%20his%20NASCAR%20lifestyle%20that%20even%20after%20his%20fund%20went%20bankrupt%20in%202019%2C%20he%20pocketed%20a%20%24200%2C000%20investment%20from%20one%20of%20his%20closest%20racing%20buddies%2C%20prosecutors%20allege.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20immediately%20spent%20%2450%2C000%20of%20the%20money%20on%20%26quot%3Bluxury%20vehicles%2C%26quot%3B%20prosecutors%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20%2415%2C000%20was%20allegedly%20diverted%20to%20%26quot%3Ba%20romantic%20partner%E2%80%94%26quot%3B%20a%20Manhattan%20woman%20who%2C%20according%20to%20court%20filings%2C%20was%20%26quot%3Bpurportedly%20engaged%20in%20the%20business%20of%20delivering%20luxury%20pet%20gift%20baskets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFranzone%20wired%20the%20now-former%20girlfriend%20%24289%2C000%20in%20fund%20assets%20between%202017%20and%202019%2C%20prosecutors%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20until%20nearly%20two%20years%20later%20when%20he%20was%20arrested%2C%20in%202021%2C%20at%20a%20palm-tree-shaded%20beachfront%20Westin%20in%20Fort%20Lauderdale%20where%20he'd%20been%20living%20for%20the%20previous%20year.%20His%20mother%20would%20end%20up%20paying%20his%20overdue%20%242%2C270%20hotel%20bill%2C%20using%20his%20father's%20credit%20card%2C%20according%20to%20court%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20his%20arrest%2C%20the%20hedge%20fund%20%E2%80%94%20which%20Franzone%20had%20been%20fighting%20for%20two%20years%20to%20keep%20afloat%20amid%20investor%20mutinees%2C%20bankruptcy%20proceedings%2C%20an%20SEC%20investigation%2C%20and%20a%20sea%20of%20litigation%20%E2%80%94%20was%20liquidated%20without%20Franzone's%20approval%2C%20by%20the%20bankruptcy%20trustee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fe177c85-e9a2-4185-ab9b-c26c26948334%5C%22%3EA%20twist%20in%20the%20track%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20twist%20in%20the%20track%20of%20this%20story%2C%20though%2C%20involving%20the%20NASCAR-worthy%20comeback%20of%20one%20of%20Franzone's%20investments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20why%20Franzone's%20%26quot%3BFF%20Fund%26quot%3B%20filed%20for%20bankruptcy%20in%202019%20remains%20in%20dispute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20say%20it%20was%20because%20Franzone%20realized%20he%20couldn't%20pay%20back%20his%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20his%20fund's%20assets%20were%20risky%2C%20failing%2C%20or%20%26quot%3Billiquid%26quot%3B%20investments%20that%20could%20not%20quickly%20converted%20into%20cash.%20The%20defense%20says%20Franzone%20had%20hoped%20bankruptcy%20would%20protect%20the%20still-viable%20fund%20from%20a%20litigious%20former%20investor%20who%20was%20trying%20to%20dissolve%20it%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEither%20way%2C%20a%20little%20over%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20the%20bankruptcy%20trustee%20liquidated%20%E2%80%94%20sold%20off%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20its%20investments%20and%20hit%20the%20jackpot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFranzone%20had%20purchased%20250%2C000%20shares%20of%20a%20Nvidia-backed%20cloud%20computing%20company%20called%20CoreWeave%20for%20%24250%2C000%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shares%20liquidated%20by%20the%20trustee%20sold%20for%20over%20%2455%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20investors%20will%20get%20more%20than%20their%20investments%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20Franzone's%20Miami%20bankruptcy%20attorney%20told%20the%20judge%20in%20that%20case%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fund%20seems%20not%20to%20be%20insolvent.%20To%20the%20contrary%2C%20it's%20done%20amazing%20because%20of%20the%20investment%20that%20was%20made%20in%20the%20company%20CoreWeave.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Franzone's%20defense%2C%20his%20lawyers%20argue%20that%20investors%20were%20warned%20in%20writing%20that%20any%20investment%20comes%20with%20risk.%20They%20were%20also%20told%20the%20fund%20would%20use%20any%20investment%20techniques%20Franzone%20felt%20were%20appropriate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20the%20case%20of%20CoreWeave%2C%20all%20of%20the%20investors%20who%20stuck%20with%20the%20fund%20%E2%80%94%20instead%20of%20writing%20their%20investment%20off%20on%20their%20taxes%20as%20a%20capital%20loss%20%E2%80%94%20have%20made%20money.%20And%20that%20includes%20Franzone%20and%20his%20own%20parents%20and%20brother%2C%20who%20remain%20investors%2C%20according%20to%20court%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20countered%20in%20a%20filing%20last%20month%20that%20it%20matters%20not%20a%20whit%20if%20CoreWeave%20did%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhether%20those%20investors%20ultimately%20recouped%20their%20losses%20years%20later%2C%20and%20only%20after%20FF%20Fund%20filed%20for%20bankruptcy%2C%20does%20not%20alter%20the%20fact%20that%20Franzone%20lied%20to%20them%2C%20deceived%20them%2C%20and%20misused%20their%20funds%20as%20part%20of%20his%20scheme%2C%26quot%3B%20prosecutors%20wrote%20the%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFranzone%20had%20hoped%20to%20argue%20that%20the%20success%20of%20his%20investment%20in%20CoreWeave%20proves%20that%20he%20never%20intended%20to%20defraud%20anyone%20and%20that%20investors%20will%20ultimately%20recoup%20any%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20the%20judge%20sided%20with%20prosecutors%20and%20barred%20the%20defense%20from%20making%20this%20argument.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20attorney%20for%20Franzone%20and%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20US%20Attorney's%20Office%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20left%20Friday%20afternoon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trial%20is%20expected%20to%20last%20three%20weeks.%20If%20convicted%2C%20Franzone%20faces%20a%20maximum%20sentence%20of%2020%20years%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhedge-fund-founder-nascar-superfan-trial-for-fraud-andrew-franzone-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744534982000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f97a733fe8d3928362e932%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhedge-fund-founder-nascar-superfan-trial-for-fraud-andrew-franzone-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Prosecutors%20say%20Andrew%20Franzone%20went%20from%20stock%20cars%20to%20stock%20fraud.%20He%20says%20his%20investment%20in%20Nvidia-backed%20CoreWeave%20shows%20his%20risk-taking%20pa