s%20is%20where%20AI%20might%20come%20in%20handy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20already%20proving%20popular.%20According%20to%20Microsoft's%202024%20Work%20Trend%20Index%2C%2075%25%20of%20global%20knowledge%20workers%2C%20such%20as%20architects%2C%20engineers%2C%20scientists%2C%20and%20lawyers%2C%20are%20using%20AI%20in%20some%20form.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Oracle%20implemented%20an%20AI%20performance%20review%20in%202023%20and%20asked%20employees%20if%20they%20liked%20it%2C%2089%25%20said%20they%20were%20willing%20to%20be%20a%20first%20adopter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20shows%20how%20much%20there%20is%20a%20need%20and%20how%20much%20people%20tend%20to%20believe%20in%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Triparna%20de%20Vreede%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20in%20the%20school%20of%20information%20systems%20and%20management%20at%20the%20University%20of%20South%20Florida's%20Muma%20College%20of%20Business%2C%20whose%20research%20focuses%20on%20human-AI%20Interaction%20and%20workplace%20well-being%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f8adb43a-9f2f-4d3f-8863-b3fa0a2f31f4%5C%22%3ETraditional%20reviews%20have%20downsides%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20de%20Vreede%2C%20performance%20reviews%20are%20%26quot%3Busually%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgendered-language-in-performance-reviews-2015-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20subjective%20exercise%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20one%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20%26quot%3Bpower%20play%26quot%3B%20between%20managers%20and%20subordinates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployees%20may%20think%20they're%20doing%20well%2C%20but%20they're%20not%20always%20aware%20of%20how%20that%20fits%20with%20the%20company's%20strategic%20direction%20or%20how%20their%20work%20contributes%20to%20the%20bottom%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20a%20recency%20bias%2C%20where%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20smaller%20things%20%26quot%3Bsort%20of%20get%20lost%20in%20the%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20de%20Vreede.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20done%20really%20great%20things%2C%20and%20then%20screwed%20up%20once%20in%20the%20past%20month%2C%20that%20bitterness%20sort%20of%20overlies%20everything%20else%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20these%20are%20the%20things%20that%20our%20traditional%20performance%20evaluations%20lack.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20performance%20reviews%20can%20help%20with%20articulation%20and%20form%20statements%20that%20align%20with%20the%20company's%20business%20strategy%20and%20ideology.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20help%20managers%20give%20better%2C%20unbiased%20feedback%2C%20which%20%26quot%3Bcreates%20a%20more%20standardized%20response%20towards%20all%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20de%20Vreede%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20they%20don't%20feel%20like%2C%20'oh%2C%20he%20likes%20you%2C%20that's%20why%20he%20gave%20you%20a%20raise'.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2287170e7d-43bf-4684-a14b-ced03d93485d%5C%22%3EAn%20objective%20listener%20is%20easier%20to%20open%20up%20to%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDe%20Vreede%20said%20that%20when%20using%20an%20AI%20performance%20review%2C%20people%20also%20tend%20to%20speak%20more.%20That's%20because%20they%20believe%20the%20AI%20will%20judge%20their%20accomplishments%20more%20fairly%20than%20their%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20necessarily%20because%20the%20manager-employee%20relationship%20is%20bad.%20The%20best%20managers%20cannot%20analyze%20their%20direct%20reports'%20emails%2C%20documents%2C%20and%20project%20management%20tools%20the%20way%20AI%20can.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20are%20often%20unreliable%20narrators.%20Dorothy%20Leidner%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20business%20and%20AI%20ethics%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Virginia%2C%20found%20this%20when%20working%20on%20a%20case%20study%20with%20Johnson%20%26amp%3B%20Johnson.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20wanted%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20digital%20skills%20the%20workforce%20had%2C%20but%20found%20that%20challenging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20turns%20out%20people%20are%20not%20great%20at%20estimating%20their%20own%20skills%2C%20and%20some%20people%20are%20overconfident%2C%20and%20then%20some%20people%20are%20underconfident%2C%26quot%3B%20Leidner%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BSo%20they%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20working%20with%20a%20vendor%20and%20designing%20an%20AI%20to%20use%20digital%20traces%20and%20HR%20data%20on%20employees%20to%20be%20able%20to%20infer%20their%20digital%20skills.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2270094363-f2b2-4972-88c6-153153626fa0%5C%22%3EWomen%20can%20find%20reviews%20challenging%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESelf-evaluations%20can%20be%20difficult%20for%20women%2C%20both%20internally%20and%20externally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWomen%20are%20consistently%20called%20more%20emotional%20and%20abrasive%2C%20whereas%20men%20are%20called%20more%20assertive%2C%26quot%3B%20de%20Vreede%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdouble-edged-sword-high-performers-face-at-work-feedback-managers-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAn%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20management%20and%20HR%20platform%20Textio%20of%2023%2C000%20performance%20reviews%20across%20250%20US%20workplaces%20last%20year%20found%20that%2038%25%20of%20language%20used%20in%20the%20performance%20reviews%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrofeminism-female-founders-execs-career-journeys-empowerment-voices-dei-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh-performing%20women%3C%2Fa%3E%20contained%20exaggerations%2C%20clich%C3%A9s%2C%20and%20fixed-mindset%20labels.%20Just%20over%20three-quarters%20of%20women%20surveyed%20said%20they'd%20been%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bemotional%2C%26quot%3B%20compared%20with%20just%2011%25%20of%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWomen%20also%20tend%20to%20downplay%20their%20achievements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fdigest%2Fdec19%2Fwomen-persistently-sell-themselves-short-same-skill-men%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20National%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Research%20in%202022%20found%20that%20women%2C%20on%20average%2C%20ranked%20their%20performance%20out%20of%20100%20as%2046%2C%20while%20men%20gave%20themselves%20an%20average%20score%20of%2061.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20women%20often%20pick%20up%20the%20slack%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freasons-why-women-burn-out-at-work-faster-than-men-2019-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etaking%20on%20invisible%20tasks%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20pile%20up%20and%20lead%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-quit-job-burned-out-chronic-stress-work-life-balance-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eburnout%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20imagine%20if%20I%20have%20an%20AI%20that%20is%20keeping%20track%20of%20all%20my%20achievements%2C%26quot%3B%20de%20Vreede%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20allows%20us%20to%20say%2C%20'oh%2C%20this%20is%20how%20we%20are%20really%20making%20a%20difference%2C'%20without%20having%20our%20imposter%20syndrome%20rising%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22547d8d95-1d3e-440d-a4fe-a35e0a7b16f6%5C%22%3EPeople%20still%20need%20to%20be%20'in%20the%20loop'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20companies%20have%20already%20created%20AI%20tools%20for%20performance%20reviews%20including%20Oracle%20and%20Textio%2C%20whose%20AI%20is%20used%20by%2025%25%20of%20Fortune%20500%20companies%20to%20analyze%20conversations%20and%20give%20feedback.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20still%20some%20way%20to%20go%20before%20AI%20self-evaluations%20are%20a%20perfect%20solution%2C%20de%20Vreede%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrivacy%20concerns%20remain%2C%20and%20companies%20need%20to%20have%20very%20clear%20policies%20about%20what%20is%20acceptable%20AI%20assistance%2C%20as%20well%20as%20be%20transparent%20about%20what%20personal%20information%20and%20work%20the%20AI%20tools%20can%20access.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDe%20Vreede%20said%20humans%20need%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bin%20the%20loop%26quot%3B%20so%20that%20softer%20skills%2C%20such%20as%20communication%2C%20warmth%2C%20and%20likeability%2C%20are%20still%20factored%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20can't%20understand%20it%20on%20its%20own%2C%20but%20AI%20can%20be%20trained%20to%20ask%20those%20questions%20so%20that%20the%20person%20can%20reflect%20and%20write%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThen%20you%20are%20truly%20capturing%20the%20human%20as%20a%20whole%20instead%20of%20just%20a%20workplace%20creature.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20major%20concern%20in%20de%20Vreede's%20view%20is%20that%20relying%20too%20much%20on%20AI%20can%20lead%20to%20people%20failing%20to%20self-reflect%20at%20all%20%E2%80%94%20rendering%20an%20evaluation%20useless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20AI%20can%20do%20the%20hard%20work%2C%20but%20you%20are%20responsible%20for%20reviewing%20the%20results%2C%20editing%20them%2C%20and%20fine-tuning%20them.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20comes%20out%20as%20your%20self-reflection%20is%20not%20just%20the%20AI's%20work%2C%20but%20a%20collaboration%20between%20you%20and%20the%20AI.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-improve-self-appraisals-performance-reviews-women-careers-promotions-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744533782000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ee54fe63d72727e1990e79%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-improve-self-appraisals-performance-reviews-women-careers-promotions-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22AI%20tools%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20improve%20self-assessments%20by%20being%20fairer%2C%20particularly%20benefiting%20women%20who%20may%20struggle%20with%20self-advocacy%2C%20researchers%20say.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ldodgson%40businessinsider.com%20(Lindsay%20Dodgson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-improve-self-appraisals-performance-reviews-women-careers-promotions-2025-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20modern%20collection%20of%20tiny%20homes%20is%20available%20in%20the%20US%20for%20the%20first%20time%20starting%20at%20%2452%2C000%20apiece%20%26amp%3Bmdash%3B%20take%20a%20look%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20medium-sized%20NIWA%20cabin%20made%20by%20Koto%20Studio%2C%20with%20aman%20exiting%20it.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f6ab343fe8d3928362974e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20medium-sized%20Niwa%20cabin%20made%20by%20Koto%2C%20a%20UK-based%20tiny-home%20company.%3Cp%3ETrent%20Bell%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUK-based%20architecture%20firm%20Koto%20makes%20cabins%20that%20are%20available%20in%20the%20US%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Niwa%20collection%20of%20minimalist%20tiny%20homes%20comes%20in%20four%20sizes%20from%2067%20to%20403%20square%20feet.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20sleek%20cabins%2C%20priced%20from%20%2452%2C000%20to%20%24187%2C000%2C%20could%20be%20used%20as%20a%20backyard%20office%20or%20a%20sauna.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECall%20it%20a%20cross-cultural%20connection%3A%20Koto%2C%20a%20UK-based%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiny-house-stay-what-its-like-weecasa-resort-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etiny-home%3C%2Fa%3E%20firm%20that%20fuses%20Scandinavian%20and%20Japanese%20design%2C%20is%20now%20delivering%20to%20US%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFounded%20in%202017%2C%20Koto%20specializes%20in%20cabins%2C%20modular%20homes%2C%20and%20sculptural%20small-scale%20architecture%20for%20residential%20and%20wellness-focused%20spaces%2C%20including%20hospitals.%20Its%20flatpack%20collection%2C%20Niwa%2C%20is%20a%20series%20of%20sustainably%20crafted%20cabins%20that%20can%20be%20delivered%20as%20panels%20and%20assembled%20on-site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20designs%20are%20like%20Ikea%2C%26quot%3B%20Koto%20cofounder%20Jonathan%20Little%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BBut%20instead%20of%20a%20box%2C%20they%20go%20into%20a%20container.%20They%20can%20be%20shipped%20around%20the%20world%20and%20installed%20pretty%20much%20anywhere.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Niwa%20comes%20in%20four%20sizes%3A%20small%20(67%20square%20feet)%2C%20medium%20(135%20square%20feet)%2C%20large%20(269%20square%20feet)%2C%20and%20extra%20large%20(403%20square%20feet).%20Prices%20range%20from%20%2452%2C000%20to%20%24187%2C000%2C%20with%20additional%20costs%20for%20custom%20features%20and%20upgrades.%20It%20is%20the%20brand's%20first%20modular%20design%20that%20is%20available%20worldwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20a%20consultation%2C%20customers%20can%20purchase%20a%20design%20license%20from%20Koto%2C%20priced%20between%20%24938%20and%20%242%2C152.%20This%20cost%20is%20not%20included%20in%20the%20cabin%20price%20and%20is%20refunded%20after%20the%20cabin%20is%20purchased.%20While%20clients%20are%20responsible%20for%20securing%20permits%20and%20hiring%20local%20contractors%20for%20site%20prep%20and%20installation%2C%20Koto%20offers%20support%20throughout%20the%20process.%20It%20can%20also%20be%20hired%20for%20concept%20site%20design%20and%20landscaping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20Niwa%20unit%20is%20constructed%20in%20a%20European%20factory%20and%20shipped%20to%20the%20US%20in%20panel%20form.%20Depending%20on%20the%20location%2C%20it%20is%20delivered%20via%20truck%2C%20helicopter%2C%20or%20boat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKoto%20began%20shipping%20Niwa%20units%20%E2%80%94%20which%20can%20be%20used%20as%20backyard%20offices%2C%20saunas%2C%20gyms%2C%20guest%20houses%2C%20Airbnbs%2C%20or%20anything%20else%20%E2%80%94%20to%20the%20US%20in%20April.%20It%20has%20already%20built%20units%20for%20customers%20in%20Massachusetts%20and%20has%20other%20planned%20installations%20in%20Los%20Angeles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETiny%20homes%20%E2%80%94%20also%20known%20as%20accessory%20dwelling%20units%2C%20or%20ADUs%20%E2%80%94%20are%20popular%20across%20the%20US.%20Several%20states%2C%20including%20California%2C%20Vermont%2C%20and%20New%20York%2C%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstates-will-compensate-you-for-building-tiny-home-adu-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoffer%20grants%20to%20help%20homeowners%20build%20them%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20their%20properties.%20For%20some%2C%20ADUs%20provide%20a%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcouple-built-adu-in-parents-backyard-couldnt-afford-traditional-house-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaffordable%20path%20to%20homeownership%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20others%2C%20they%20offer%20an%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fbusinessinsider.com%2Fmoved-into-california-adu-save-money-retire-early-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincome-generating%20opportunity%20through%20rentals%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0or%20a%20practical%20way%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-builds-adu-office-in-backyard-cost-benefits-property-value-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecreate%20additional%20living%20space%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0when%20the%20square%20footage%20in%20a%20main%20house%20is%20limited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20seeing%20such%20a%20diverse%20requirement%20for%20our%20cabins%2C%20both%20from%20private%20individuals%20all%20the%20way%20up%20to%20hotel%20owners%2C%26quot%3B%20Little%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20a%20look%20inside%20the%20three%20Niwa%20models%20available%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20design%20of%20the%20Niwa%20cabins%20channels%20clean%2C%20contemporary%20minimalism.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20medium-sized%20Koto%20cabin.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f6aba0a466d2b74ab2b050%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221668%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20medium-sized%20Koto%20cabin.%3Cp%3EJoanna%20Kossak%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20Niwa%20unit%20has%20essential%20features%2C%20lighting%2C%20and%20a%20heating%20and%20cooling%20system.%20Depending%20on%20the%20size%20of%20the%20unit%20ordered%2C%20a%20bathroom%20or%20kitchenette%20can%20also%20be%20included.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EKoto%20designed%20the%20Niwa%20collection%20of%20tiny%20homes%20with%20nature%20in%20mind.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20exterior%20of%20a%20tiny%20Koto%20home%20surrounded%20by%20trees%20and%20flowers.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f6ac14c6ad288d147dae5c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Koto%20cabin.%3Cp%3EEdvinas%20Bruzas%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENiwa%20units%20are%20designed%20to%20blend%20into%20their%20surroundings%20and%20support%20both%20on-grid%20and%20off-grid%20living.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKoto%20builds%20its%20cabins%20using%20natural%20materials.%20The%20structure%20is%20built%20with%20sustainably%20sourced%20timber.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20exterior%20cladding%20is%20made%20from%20Shou%20Sugi%20Ban%20timber%20%E2%80%94%20wood%20treated%20with%20a%20traditional%20Japanese%20charring%20method%20that%20makes%20it%20fire-resistant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKoto%20builds%20its%20cabins%20using%20natural%2C%20sustainably%20sourced%20materials.%20The%20main%20structure%20is%20made%20from%20responsibly%20harvested%20timber%2C%20while%20the%20exterior%20features%20Shou%20Sugi%20Ban%20%E2%80%94%20wood%20charred%20using%20a%20traditional%20Japanese%20method%20for%20added%20durability%20and%20fire%20resistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInterior%20finishes%20vary%20by%20unit%20type%3B%20studio%20cabins%20and%20units%20people%20can%20sleep%20in%20typically%20feature%20oak%20or%20birch%20plywood%2C%20while%20saunas%20are%20finished%20with%20hemlock%2C%20spruce%2C%20or%20cedar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EKoto%20wants%20the%20people%20who%20buy%20its%20homes%20to%20reconnect%20with%20the%20outdoors.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%229528%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Koto%20tiny%20home%20in%20the%20woods.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f6ad3ca466d2b74ab2b0cd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226328%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAnother%20view%20of%20the%20medium-sized%20Niwa%20cabin.%3Cp%3ETrent%20Bell%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELittle%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Niwa's%20nature-centered%20design%20was%20inspired%20by%20his%20own%20move%20from%20busy%20London%20to%20Norway%2C%20where%20the%20pace%20of%20life%20is%20slower%2C%20and%20there's%20a%20greater%20emphasis%20on%20the%20outdoors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLondon%20has%20a%20real%20fast-paced%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20work%20a%20lot%20of%20hours%2C%20then%20go%20home%2C%20rest%2C%20and%20do%20the%20same%20thing%20the%20next%20day.%20Moving%20to%20Norway%20was%20the%20opposite.%20It%20was%20like%2C%20yes%2C%20get%20your%20work%20done%2C%20but%20be%20outside%20with%20your%20friends%20and%20family%2C%20be%20in%20the%20woods%20in%20nature.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EEach%20cabin%20can%20be%20installed%20in%20under%20a%20month.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228976%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20medium-sized%20NIWA%20cabin.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f6adbac6ad288d147daec2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225810%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAnother%20angle%20of%20the%20medium-sized%20Niwa%20cabin.%3Cp%3ETrent%20Bell%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENiwa%20cabins%20typically%20take%20eight%20to%2012%20weeks%20to%20manufacture%2C%20with%20shipping%20adding%20another%20two%20to%20four%20weeks%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20destination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShipping%20costs%20vary%20by%20location%2C%20but%20the%20company%20estimates%20US%20deliveries%20cost%20around%20%249%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Koto's%20website%2C%20installation%20for%20each%20unit%20may%20take%20four%20to%2014%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20collection%20comes%20in%20four%20sizes%3A%20small%2C%20medium%2C%20large%2C%20and%20extra-large.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%203-D%20rendering%20of%205%20NIWA%20cabins.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f6ae76c6ad288d147daedf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222277%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20cabin%20on%20the%20far%20left%20is%20a%20large-sized%20Niwa%20model%2C%20while%20the%20one%20on%20the%20far%20right%20is%20a%20sauna.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Koto%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Koto%2C%20the%20Niwa%20small%20unit%2C%20which%20measures%20about%2067%20square%20feet%2C%20is%20ideal%20for%20use%20as%20a%20studio%20or%20sauna.%20The%20ceiling%20height%20ranges%20from%205.9%20feet%20at%20its%20lowest%20point%20to%2011.8%20feet%20at%20its%20peak.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20design%20license%20fee%20for%20this%20unit%20is%20about%20%24940%2C%20and%20the%20base%20price%20starts%20at%20%2455%2C286.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20cabins'%20interior%20design%20is%20simple%20yet%20stylish.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20interior%20of%20a%20NIWA%20cabin%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f6aeb63fe8d39283629819%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20kitchenette%20in%20a%20Niwa%20cabin.%3Cp%3ESimon%20Bevan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20interior%20finishes%20of%20the%20Niwa%20units%20typically%20feature%2