t%20employees%20whose%20lives%20have%20been%20upended%20by%20DOGE's%20moves%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-agencies-musk-doge-targeted-list-2025-2%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThat%2520includes%2520workers%2520at%2520the%2CMedicaid%2520Services%252C%2520the%2520Internal%2520Revenue%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshrink%20federal%20agencies%20and%20cut%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20changes%20are%20creating%20economic%20uncertainty%20for%20many%20Americans%2C%20especially%20those%20close%20to%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20administration%20official%20told%20BI%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20State%20Department%20is%20committed%20to%20offering%20additional%20resources%20and%20benefits%20to%20ensure%20the%20safety%20and%20security%20of%20USAID%20employees%20transitioning%20from%20service.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22450acb24-0f59-4106-b77d-9be4d8405fd8%5C%22%3EReniers%20thought%20she%20was%20'essential'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20DOGE%20arrived%20at%20USAID%20in%20January%2C%20chaos%20ensued.%C2%A0Employees%20received%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-federal-workers-employee-buyout-read-opm-letter-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efork%20in%20the%20road%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20email%20offering%20full%20pay%20and%20benefits%20through%20September%20to%20those%20who%20voluntarily%20resigned.%20They%20were%20temporarily%20locked%20out%20of%20computer%20systems%20and%20told%20to%20stay%20home%20as%20the%20Washington%2C%20DC%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fusaid-workers-stay-home-elon-musk-trump-shut-down-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eheadquarters%20was%20shut%20down%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20Reniers%20said%20leadership%20initially%20told%20her%20that%20she%20was%20an%20%26quot%3Bessential%26quot%3B%20employee.%20Reniers%20rose%20to%20be%20division%20chief%20for%20Europe%20at%20USAID's%20Bureau%20of%20Humanitarian%20Assistance.%20The%20bureau%20provides%20food%2C%20water%20and%20sanitation%2C%20shelter%2C%20and%20emergency%20healthcare%20to%20people%20facing%20various%20crises%20around%20the%20world.%20Reniers'%20division%20covered%20Ukraine%2C%20Turkey%2C%20and%20other%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20made%20Reniers%20think%20she%20was%20safe%20from%20widespread%20layoffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20I%20did%20not%20take%20the%20Fork%2C%20and%20now%20I'm%20shooting%20myself%20in%20the%20foot%2C%26quot%3B%20Reniers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2024%2C%20Reniers%20received%20an%20email%20stating%20that%20she%20was%20being%20placed%20on%20administrative%20leave%20and%20that%20a%20subordinate%20would%20take%20over%20her%20duties.%20On%20March%2027%2C%20she%20was%20informed%20that%20her%20position%20was%20being%20abolished.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20email%20asked%20employees%20to%20volunteer%20to%20%26quot%3Bsupport%20critical%20work%26quot%3B%20while%20the%20agency%20shifts%20tasks%20to%20the%20State%20Department.%20Reniers%20said%20she%20plans%20to%20return%20for%20a%20few%20weeks%20because%20her%20colleagues%20are%20burned%20out%20and%20need%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecretary%20of%20State%20Marco%20Rubio%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Fon-delivering-an-america-first-foreign-assistance-program%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20March%2028%20notified%20Congress%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20reorganization%20and%20previously%20said%20about%2083%25%20of%20the%20agency's%20programs%20had%20been%20cut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223ee15148-a157-4b32-93f4-96f850aef28a%5C%22%3EBackup%20plan%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Reniers%20said%20she's%20had%20panic%20attacks%20while%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20a%20backup%20financial%20plan.%20She%20wasn't%20planning%20to%20retire%20for%20at%20least%20another%20four%20years%2C%20when%20her%20son%20will%20graduate%20from%20high%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20Reniers%20won't%20reach%2020%20years%20of%20federal%20service%2C%20she%20estimated%20her%20pension%20benefits%20will%20be%20about%20half%20of%20what%20she%20would've%20qualified%20for%20in%20November.%20For%20foreign%20service%20employees%20with%20less%20than%20two%20decades%20of%20service%2C%20monthly%20retirement%20calculations%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fafsa.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fbenefits-at-retirement-resignation-and-separation-2025-02.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efollow%20this%20formula%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20an%20employee's%20highest%20annual%20salary%2C%20multiplied%20by%2020%2C%20multiplied%20by%201%25%2C%20and%20divided%20by%2012.%20Reniers%20earned%20%24177%2C200%20a%20year%2C%20making%20her%20new%20pension%20a%20little%20under%20%243%2C000%20a%20month%20under%20that%20formula.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20she%20had%20made%20it%20to%2020%20years%2C%20that%201%25%20would%20instead%20have%20been%201.7%25.%20That%20higher%20rate%2C%20along%20with%20a%20supplemental%20annuity%2C%20would%20have%20given%20her%20a%20pension%20of%20around%20%246%2C000%20a%20month%20%E2%80%94%20about%20double%20what%20she%20expects%20to%20get%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20while%20she%20could%20have%20retired%20at%20any%20time%20after%20her%2020th%20anniversary%20and%20received%20that%20full%20pension%2C%20she%20won't%20be%20eligible%20for%20the%20smaller%20pension%20until%20she%20turns%2062.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReniers%20will%20receive%20a%20severance%20package%20worth%20one%20year's%20annual%20salary%20and%20is%20also%20planning%20to%20sell%20an%20apartment%20she%20owns%20in%20Belgium%20to%20help%20establish%20a%20financial%20safety%20net%20for%20monthly%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20lucky%20I%20have%20that%2C%20so%20I%20can%20make%20sure%20to%20keep%20my%20home%20in%20Maryland%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BHow%20do%20I%20find%20a%20job%20with%20a%20similar%20salary%20when%20I'm%2053%20with%20a%20disability%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20R